# .env.example — committed template (per .gitignore !.env.example exception)
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (which IS gitignored) and fill values:
#   cp .env.example .env.local && chmod 600 .env.local
#   git check-ignore .env.local   # should print ".env.local"
#
# This file (.env.example) is safe to commit — it contains no secrets.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API-key policy (consensus — D-132)
#
#  🏗️  Build-time / content pipeline (OCR, vision, translation, knowledge
#      mapping, Stage 4 textbook generation): runs via Claude Code
#      (Max plan) — NO external API keys needed. Don't add pipeline keys here.
#
#  🌐  Runtime / web-app AI (chat, tutor, glossary, quiz, future AI-learning):
#      uses external APIs; those keys live in `apps/web/.env.local`
#      (DEEPSEEK_API_KEY default, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY optional toggle) — NOT here.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Legacy notes:
#   - Phase 1 Mistral OCR (MISTRAL_API_KEY) was removed in Session 63
#     (D-110 / D-113) and is no longer used.
#   - A few Stage-2-era scripts under scripts/ still reference
#     ANTHROPIC_API_KEY; they are historical and NOT the go-forward path
#     (Stage 4+ pipeline runs via Claude Code, per D-132).
#
# This root template currently declares no required variables.
